so does curlie require curl installed?

Gemini said
Yes, curlie absolutely requires curl to be installed on your system.

Think of curlie as a high-end "skin" or a translator. It provides the user-friendly interface and the beautiful, formatted output, but it doesn't actually know how to talk to the internet on its own. When you hit enter on a curlie command, it translates your input into a standard curl command and executes it in the background.

Why this architecture matters
This "wrapper" approach is actually its greatest strength for a few reasons:

Reliability: It inherits decades of curl's stability. If a feature works in curl, it works in curlie.

Feature Parity: You can use any niche curl flag (like --resolve or --interface) that more modern tools like HTTPie might not have implemented yet.

The "Exit" Strategy: If you ever need to share a command with a teammate who doesn't have curlie, you can simply run your command with the --curl flag, and it will print the exact curl syntax for you to copy-paste.

A Quick Visual of the Workflow
User Input: You type a simple, HTTPie-style command.

The Translation: curlie converts that into a complex curl string.

The Engine: curl (which must be in your system PATH) executes the network request.

The Result: curlie captures the raw text from curl, colors it, formats the JSON, and hands it back to you.

How to check if you're ready
If you are on a Mac or Linux, you almost certainly have curl already. You can verify this by typing:

Bash
curl --version
If that returns a version number, you are all set to install and use curlie.

